# Docker and CI

## Docker

- **Base image:** `ruby:3.3.11-slim` with multi-stage build
- **CUPS client:** `cups-client` in the base image so `lp(1)` is available for receipt printing
- **Node:** Installed via nodenv (Node 24.x) for asset compilation
- **Yarn:** Use `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` — never modify `yarn.lock` in Docker builds
- **Assets:** Precompiled with `SECRET_KEY_BASE_DUMMY=1`
- **Runtime:** Non-root `rails` user; entrypoint at `bin/docker-entrypoint`

## docker-compose

**Development** (`docker-compose.yml`): `db` (postgres:16), `redis`, `web`, `sidekiq` — app image is built from the Dockerfile; source bind-mounted at `/rails`.

**Tests and lint** (`docker-compose.test.yml`): no `build` — `ruby:3.3.11-bookworm` with the repo mounted at `/rails`, named volumes for Bundler and RuboCop cache. Services use `gunky-test-*` container names and an isolated network (`gunky-test-network`).

- `docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml run --rm app` — `bin/rails db:test:prepare test`
- `docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml run --rm lint` — `bin/rubocop` (RuboCop cache under `tmp/rubocop` on a named volume)

First run installs Debian packages once (marker on the bundle volume) then `bundle install`.

- The `migrate` service runs under the `tools` profile

## GitHub Actions

- **ci.yml:** Runs on push/PR to `main`; sets up PostgreSQL 16 and Redis 7 as service containers; runs `bin/rails test`
- **release.yml:** Triggered by `v*` tags; runs tests then builds and pushes Docker image to `ghcr.io`
- Uses `ruby/setup-ruby` with bundler-cache and `actions/setup-node` with yarn cache
- Concurrency: cancels in-progress runs for the same ref
